{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"603ac562-6803-4773-a97b-0d4c48a84ee7","content":"Here's the architecture and plan for your RAG-based Q&A feature:\n\n---\n\n## Architecture Overview\n\n```\n┌─────────────┐      ┌──────────────────┐      ┌────────────────┐\n│  Docs/*.md  │─────▶│ Ingestion Service │─────▶│ Vector Store   │\n└─────────────┘      │ (chunk + embed)   │      │ (in-memory or  │\n                     └──────────────────┘      │  external DB)  │\n                                                └───────┬────────┘\n                                                        │\n┌─────────────┐      ┌──────────────────┐              │\n│  User Query │─────▶│  Query Endpoint  │──── search ──┘\n└─────────────┘      │  POST /ask       │\n                     └───────┬──────────┘\n                             │ top-K chunks + question\n                             ▼\n                     ┌──────────────────┐\n                     │   LLM (OpenAI /  │\n                     │   Azure OpenAI)  │\n                     └──────────────────┘\n```\n\n## Key Components\n\n| Layer | Responsibility | Suggested Package |\n|-------|---------------|-------------------|\n| **Chunking** | Split markdown by heading/paragraph, ~500 tokens per chunk with overlap | `Microsoft.Extensions.AI` or custom splitter |\n| **Embedding** | Convert chunks → vectors | `Azure.AI.OpenAI` (text-embedding-3-small) |\n| **Vector Store** | Store & similarity-search embeddings | `Microsoft.Extensions.VectorData` + in-memory provider (or Qdrant/Azure AI Search for prod) |\n| **Query orchestration** | Embed question → retrieve top-K → build prompt → call LLM | `Microsoft.Extensions.AI.ChatCompletion` |\n| **API surface** | `POST /api/documents/ingest` and `POST /api/ask` | ASP.NET Controllers |\n\n## Endpoints\n\n1. **`POST /api/documents/ingest`** — reads `Docs/*.md`, chunks, embeds, stores vectors. Idempotent (clears & rebuilds).\n2. **`POST /api/ask`** — accepts `{ \"question\": \"...\" }`, returns `{ \"answer\": \"...\", \"sources\": [...] }`.\n\n## Chunking Strategy\n\n- Split on `## ` headings first (section-level).\n- If a section exceeds ~500 tokens, split further on double-newline paragraphs.\n- Each chunk carries metadata: `{ fileName, heading, chunkIndex }`.\n\n## Data Flow (Query)\n\n1. Embed the user's question.\n2. Cosine-similarity search → top 3–5 chunks.\n3. Build a system prompt: *\"Answer using only the provided context.\"*\n4. Send context + question to LLM.\n5. Return answer + source metadata.\n\n## Considerations\n\n- **Startup ingestion**: optionally auto-ingest on app start via `IHostedService`.\n- **Config**: API keys and model names in `appsettings.json` / env vars.\n- **Testing**: chunk logic is pure and unit-testable; LLM calls can be mocked via `IChatClient`.\n- **Scaling**: swap in-memory vector store for Azure AI Search or Qdrant when docs grow.\n\n---\n\nWould you like me to implement this?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"44d6985b-3a79-4d1f-a2a8-1c657934764b","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"Now I have a good understanding of the project. It's a minimal .NET 10 Web API with a `Docs/` folder containing markdown files. Let me create a comprehensive architecture plan for a RAG-based Q&A feature.","outputTokens":904,"requestId":"2BC1:32F6A4:19A1307:1CC4191:69FD4504"},"id":"0956a3bc-1b1e-4708-918e-0550729d549c","timestamp":"2026-05-08T02:06:15.563Z","parentId":"827b83d1-f9bd-44f5-b786-5257b7ea6a4c"}
